\[
\Delta U_{\mathrm{m}} = -a\left(\frac{1}{V_{2}}-\frac{1}{V_{1}}\right)
= a\left(\frac{1}{V_{1}}-\frac{1}{V_{2}}\right)
\]

For nitrogen, \(a = 1.370\;\text{L}^{2}\text{bar mol}^{-2}\).

Convert \(a\) to SI units:

\[
a = 1.370\;\text{L}^{2}\text{bar mol}^{-2}
   = 1.370\times(10^{-3}\,\text{m}^{3})^{2}\times10^{5}\,\text{Pa}
   = 0.137\;\text{Pa m}^{6}\text{mol}^{-2}
\]

Initial and final molar volumes:

\[
V_{1}=1.00\;\text{dm}^{3}=0.001\;\text{m}^{3},\qquad
V_{2}=24.8\;\text{dm}^{3}=0.0248\;\text{m}^{3}
\]

\[
\frac{1}{V_{1}}-\frac{1}{V_{2}}
= \frac{1}{0.001}-\frac{1}{0.0248}
= 1000-40.3226
= 959.6774\;\text{m}^{-3}
\]

Hence

\[
\Delta U_{\mathrm{m}}
= 0.137\;\text{Pa m}^{6}\text{mol}^{-2}\times 959.6774\;\text{m}^{-3}
= 131.5\;\text{J mol}^{-1}
\]

\[
\boxed{131}\ \text{J mol}^{-1}
\]

