The rotational constant \(B\) is half the line spacing:

\[
B=\frac{\Delta\nu}{2}= \frac{6.26\times10^{11}\,\text{Hz}}{2}=3.13\times10^{11}\,\text{Hz}
\]

For a rigid rotor

\[
B=\frac{h}{8\pi^{2}I}\quad\Longrightarrow\quad I=\frac{h}{8\pi^{2}B}
\]

\[
I=\frac{6.626\times10^{-34}\,\text{J\,s}}{8\pi^{2}\,(3.13\times10^{11}\,\text{Hz})}
   \approx 2.68\times10^{-47}\,\text{kg\,m}^{2}
\]

The reduced mass of \(\mathrm{H}^{35}\mathrm{Cl}\) is

\[
\mu=\frac{m_{\mathrm H}\,m_{\mathrm{Cl}}}{m_{\mathrm H}+m_{\mathrm{Cl}}}
   =\frac{(1.007825\,u)(34.968852\,u)}{1.007825\,u+34.968852\,u}
   \approx 1.63\times10^{-27}\,\text{kg}
\]

The bond length \(r\) follows from \(I=\mu r^{2}\):

\[
r=\sqrt{\frac{I}{\mu}}
  =\sqrt{\frac{2.68\times10^{-47}}{1.63\times10^{-27}}}
  \approx 1.28\times10^{-10}\,\text{m}
  =128\,\text{pm}
\]

\[
\boxed{128}\text{ pm}
\]

