llm_answer:
The cubic BN crystal has the diamond structure.  
For a cubic cell of side \(a=3.63\;\text{\AA}=3.63\times10^{-8}\;\text{cm}\):

1. **Number of formula units per cell**  
   The fcc lattice has 4 lattice points per cell and the basis contains one B and one N atom.  
   \[
   N_{\text{BN}} = 4\;\text{formula units}
   \]

2. **Mass of one unit cell**  
   \[
   M_{\text{cell}} = N_{\text{BN}}\,(M_{\text{B}}+M_{\text{N}})
   =4\,(10.81+14.01)\;\text{g mol}^{-1}
   =99.28\;\text{g mol}^{-1}
   \]
   Convert to grams per cell:
   \[
   m_{\text{cell}}=\frac{99.28}{N_A}
   =\frac{99.28}{6.022\times10^{23}}
   =1.648\times10^{-22}\;\text{g}
   \]

3. **Volume of the unit cell**  
   \[
   V_{\text{cell}}=a^{3}=(3.63\times10^{-8}\;\text{cm})^{3}
   =4.784\times10^{-23}\;\text{cm}^{3}
   \]

4. **Density**  
   \[
   \rho=\frac{m_{\text{cell}}}{V_{\text{cell}}}
   =\frac{1.648\times10^{-22}\;\text{g}}
          {4.784\times10^{-23}\;\text{cm}^{3}}
   =3.45\;\text{g cm}^{-3}
   \]

\[
\boxed{3.45}\;\text{g cm}^{-3}
\]

