The van der Waals equation is  

\[
\left(P+\frac{a n^{2}}{V^{2}}\right)(V-nb)=nRT
\]

---

**1.  Convert the given data to consistent units**

\[
\begin{aligned}
V &= 1.000\ \text{m}^{3}=1000\ \text{dm}^{3} \\
m &= 92.4\ \text{kg} \\
M_{\text{N}_2} &= 28.014\ \text{g mol}^{-1}=0.028014\ \text{kg mol}^{-1} \\
n &= \frac{m}{M_{\text{N}_2}}
      =\frac{92.4}{0.028014}\approx 3.2985\times10^{3}\ \text{mol}
\end{aligned}
\]

---

**2.  Compute the van der Waals correction terms**

\[
\begin{aligned}
\frac{a n^{2}}{V^{2}}
&= \frac{1.352\ \text{atm dm}^{6}\text{mol}^{-2}\,(3.2985\times10^{3}\ \text{mol})^{2}}
        {(1000\ \text{dm}^{3})^{2}}  \\
&\approx 14.71\ \text{atm}
\\[4pt]
n b &= 3.2985\times10^{3}\ \text{mol}\,(0.0387\ \text{dm}^{3}\text{mol}^{-1})
      \approx 127.65\ \text{dm}^{3}
\\[4pt]
V-nb &= 1000-127.65 \approx 872.35\ \text{dm}^{3}
\end{aligned}
\]

---

**3.  Evaluate the right‑hand side**

\[
nRT = (3.2985\times10^{3}\ \text{mol})\,(0.082057\ \text{dm}^{3}\text{atm mol}^{-1}\text{K}^{-1})\,(500\ \text{K})
      \approx 1.3523\times10^{5}\ \text{atm dm}^{3}
\]

---

**4.  Solve for \(P\)**  

\[
P+\frac{a n^{2}}{V^{2}}
   = \frac{nRT}{V-nb}
   = \frac{1.3523\times10^{5}}{872.35}
   \approx 155.02\ \text{atm}
\]

\[
P = 155.02\ \text{atm} - 14.71\ \text{atm}
   \approx 140.3\ \text{atm}
\]

---

\[
\boxed{140.3}\ \text{atm}
\]

